Great fast-served food that beats the competition (Shake Shack, etc.). With a simple menu that has options for everyone, including vegetarians, Thunder Bun delivers the goods. Definitely worth a visit to the concourse level of One New York Plaza.

We love this spot! You can immediately taste the difference in their fresh ingredients- it makes a huge difference during the meal and after. Nothing is overly greasy like other "fast food" spots and we couldn't stop talking about it. The menu has a wide variety of choices which made it difficult to decide what we wanted but we definitely don't regret our order! The chicken is crispy, juicy and really fresh, the fries are amazing and the atmosphere was clean and lively! The staff is really helpful and willing to accommodate your needs. We can't wait to go back here- it's definitely a hidden gem in the Financial District.

It’s nicely stationed in the ground level of a massive building and they offer inexpensive menu items. It’s very affordable and high quality. They offer customers a ton of sides to choose from that are both plentiful and tasty.

I loved how the menu is super easy to follow AND has pictures! It’s super helpful for me to see what looks good or help me decide what I’m craving. We tried The Thunder Bun and I loved the small onion bits in my burger. Every bite had onions and I didn’t feel like I had to go searching for them. The Chicken Schnipp has a $1 special until March 8th. You would need the promo code SCHNNYCFIDI when you download the Ritual App. We also tried the Cremini Mushroom and the Buffalo. Both were really tasty. We ordered the Chicken Fingers and they tasted so good with the dipping sauces. There’s so many to choose from- and don’t get me started on the sides! They have a long list of sides to chose from and you have to get the waffle fries! Overall, the meal was affordable and had something for everyone. I enjoyed my visit and I wish it was closer to where I worked to eat this on a daily.

Great burgers and amazing sides. For $10 you can get a decent sized burger and 2 sides. The corn was amazing, while the onion rings I had were so-so. Only minor complaint was that sauces were extra unless you get the chicken fingers. Overall great though!

I lover burgers. Period. As a self-identified burger aficionado, I can say that Thunder Bun has some of the best burgers I've had in a while. Despite the location, Thunder Bun's burgers a lot more affordable than most others put there. Today I had their Sweet Heat and Buffalo Tofu sandwiches and I gotta say that the Buffalo Tofu has me sold on crispy tofu (not a tofu fan). I definitely look forward to coming here again! Great prices and AMAZING burgers!

Good selection of burgers and chicken sandwiches, as well as vegetarian options.  They also have a good selection of sides besides the classic waffle fries and onion rings, adding options like broccoli and Mexican corn.  I’d suggest you try the classic cheeseburger aka the schnipps, and give the chicken sandwiches a go, as I’m sure there’s at least one that will suit anyone’s palate.  If you’re a fan of buffalo wings and blue cheese, do try their chicken sandwich version, it’s pretty good!  If you’re in the area and you’re looking for a decent place where you won’t spend a fortune Thunder Bun (Schnippers lil brother) might be what you’re looking for!

The truth is, it's not hard to find a satisfying fast-food style burger any more. What sets Thunder Bun apart is their excellent sides. Choose a sandwich (I recommend the cheeseburger or the spicy chicken) but be sure to get the charred broccoli, the corn esquites, or the kale salad - all are fantastic.  The name is a bit unfortunate and might make you think of a forgotten James Bond villain, circa 1965.  It's worth looking past it.
Love the food specially the fingers
You don’t understand how good the street corn side is. It’s a little spicy, FYI. Burger (they’re all slightly over slider size) + 2 sides is a good deal and the perfect meal.

I went at the peak of lunch at 1pm, and though it was crowded, Shae (the manager) and her crew kept the line moving quickly.  I ordered a Cremini Mushroom Burger, corn salad, pasta salad, and waffle fries.  The burger was juicy and cooked Medium, as requested. There was a very nice amount of mushrooms and truffle aioli.  The waffle fries were hot and crispy, and the macaroni salad was good. The absolute star was the corn salad, though. Each fresh, crunchy, sweet, charred kernal was covered in a delicious spicy seasoning. This will be my Go-To side dish on every visit from now on! It

Very good burger at a great price and in a fab location for a bite before or after the Staten Island Ferry. Burgers, chicken sandwiches and veggie sandwiches available with a choice of sides and dipping sauces, service with a smile too 😁 thanks 🙏🏻

It’s a fun family friendly activity or great date if you go at sunset! Just make sure you get to TB before they close. Love all the sandwich options and the market sides, the menu truly offers something for everybody!

This is a gem of a find. New York lunch combined with classic fast food burger. The choice is amazing and the veggie options pleased my picky partner which is saying something. 10/10 would burger again.

A great place to stop for burgers, chicken sandwiches, fries, onion rings and shakes.  Everything we tried on the menu was pretty tasty and lots of interesting combinations.  The staff were very helpful in answering our questions about specific allergens too.

This place is awesome!  The chicken sandwiches and burgers are flavorful and very satisfying. The fries and market sides are delicious too. It’s pricey and portions are small so it’s definitely a once-in-a-while restaurant. You would have a hard time eating healthy here!

Great food! Very affordable especially if you are on a budget. Any sandwich $5.50, add a side $8, add 2 sides $10. You can't go wrong here. I got might favorite The Grilled Angeleno. Grilled chicken, smashed avocado, plum tomatoes, pickled red onions and brown mustard relish with waffle fries. You can substitute the grilled chicken for fried if you like. They also have roasted sweet potato wedges..Amazing! Veggie options are available as well.

For $10 you get a freshly cooked burger or chicken sandwich and 2 market sides that are made daily!!!! The bacon ranch potato salad is to die for!!!!! The bacon is cooked fresh everyday! It's not bacon bits!!! The honey roasted carrots made me like carrots again!!!!! Jonathan schnipper searched high and low for the perfect pasta for the best macaroni salad!!!!! It's great tasting food where they don't try to empty your pockets!!!
